00:06.800 --> 00:08.840
It's very simple. They want to drive them out.

00:08.840 --> 00:18.060
Well, ladies and gentlemen,

00:18.060 --> 00:19.520
welcome to the Intercontinental.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.120
My name is Tom Switzer.

00:21.120 --> 00:22.560
I'm the executive director at

00:22.560 --> 00:24.440
the Center for Independent Studies.

00:24.440 --> 00:27.000
Now, for those of you who don't know much about CIS,

00:27.000 --> 00:29.320
we're a public policy research organization.

00:29.320 --> 00:31.640
We're just based up the road on Macquarie Street,

00:31.640 --> 00:34.900
and we are primarily focused on

00:34.900 --> 00:37.640
tackling our nation's great public policy challenges.

00:37.640 --> 00:39.360
So we're interested in economics,

00:39.360 --> 00:44.160
education, energy, housing affordability,

00:44.160 --> 00:47.440
intergenerational matters, aboriginal affairs.

00:47.440 --> 00:49.280
But we're also very much engaged in

00:49.280 --> 00:51.080
the foreign policy debates,

00:51.080 --> 00:54.000
and that brings us to this evening's event.

00:54.000 --> 00:56.800
Now, I should stress from the outset that I think it's

00:56.800 --> 00:58.760
probably fair to say that this crisis

00:58.760 --> 01:01.720
between Israel and Gaza in the Middle East,

01:01.720 --> 01:03.640
it's probably the most vexed issue

01:03.640 --> 01:06.920
in international relations in 2024.

01:06.920 --> 01:10.560
In a month's time, we'll hear from Brett Stevens,

01:10.560 --> 01:11.880
the award-winning columnist at

01:11.880 --> 01:14.760
the New York Times formerly with the Wall Street Journal.

01:14.760 --> 01:17.240
He'll be speaking in solid defense of

01:17.240 --> 01:20.520
Israel's military campaign in Gaza.

01:20.520 --> 01:23.840
But tonight, we will hear a radically different view.

01:23.840 --> 01:26.440
We at CIS believe that it's very important,

01:26.480 --> 01:29.760
especially for a classical liberal organization like CIS,

01:29.760 --> 01:32.880
to hear both sides of any debate.

01:32.880 --> 01:35.160
Now, John Mirshimer is without doubt

01:35.160 --> 01:37.280
one of the most distinguished professors

01:37.280 --> 01:39.400
of political science in the world.

01:39.400 --> 01:41.400
He's been a professor of political science

01:41.400 --> 01:45.520
at the University of Chicago for more than four decades.

01:45.520 --> 01:48.240
He's the author of many prominent and influential books,

01:48.240 --> 01:52.400
most notably the Tragedy of Great Power Politics,

01:52.400 --> 01:55.040
that was published in 2001,

01:55.040 --> 01:56.440
and Foreign Affairs Magazine,

01:56.440 --> 01:59.400
the prestigious New York-based journal of opinion

01:59.400 --> 02:01.560
on international affairs.

02:01.560 --> 02:06.000
It ranks Mirshimer's Great Power Thesis

02:06.000 --> 02:09.600
as one of the three most influential foreign policy

02:09.600 --> 02:13.000
theses of the post-Coll war era.

02:13.000 --> 02:16.520
John, as Foreign Affairs has actually acknowledged,

02:16.520 --> 02:21.520
is quote, one of the most famous political scientists

02:22.320 --> 02:25.080
in history, extraordinary rap,

02:25.080 --> 02:28.960
one of the most famous political scientists in history.

02:28.960 --> 02:30.960
And that review of John's latest book

02:30.960 --> 02:32.240
was written by a critic.

02:33.640 --> 02:35.880
John is also, I think it's fair to say,

02:35.880 --> 02:38.840
a global sensation in the digital world.

02:38.840 --> 02:43.840
In fact, 19 of his debates and interviews on YouTube

02:44.720 --> 02:48.400
have each attracted more than one million views,

02:48.400 --> 02:50.320
extraordinary, extraordinary.

02:50.320 --> 02:54.080
And I should stress that since he quite correctly predicted

02:54.080 --> 02:57.680
that the US-led invasion of Iraq would be not just

02:57.680 --> 03:02.080
unnecessary, but a strategic blunder of epic proportions.

03:02.080 --> 03:05.600
So it's an extraordinary reach and influence for John.

03:05.600 --> 03:07.880
And with that, it's my great pleasure,

03:07.880 --> 03:10.960
on behalf of CIS, to welcome Professor John Mirshimer

03:10.960 --> 03:12.120
back to CIS.

03:12.120 --> 03:17.120
Thank you very much for the kind words, Tom.

03:17.120 --> 03:18.520
It's great to be back here.

03:18.520 --> 03:20.040
Great to see Tom again.

03:20.040 --> 03:23.000
And thank you all for coming out to hear me speak tonight.

03:24.600 --> 03:27.960
As everybody knows, since October 7th,

03:27.960 --> 03:31.960
the Middle East has been turned upside down.

03:31.960 --> 03:34.280
I think before October 7th,

03:34.280 --> 03:38.680
almost everybody thought that the Middle East

03:38.680 --> 03:40.560
was a quite stable area.

03:40.560 --> 03:42.560
There were no big problems.

03:42.560 --> 03:44.440
Then October 7th happened,

03:44.440 --> 03:48.720
and it looks like nothing but trouble today

03:48.720 --> 03:51.800
and for as far as the eye can see.

03:51.800 --> 03:56.960
And what I'd like to do is analyze what has happened

03:56.960 --> 03:59.280
since October 7th.

03:59.280 --> 04:02.640
I'd like to talk about the causes of the trouble,

04:02.640 --> 04:07.520
where we are today, and where we're going.

04:07.520 --> 04:13.520
And in pursuit of that, I want to break my talk down this way.

04:13.520 --> 04:18.800
First, I want to focus on analyzing the conflict in Gaza,

04:18.800 --> 04:23.400
mainly between Israel and the Palestinians,

04:23.400 --> 04:25.440
or Israel and Hamas.

04:25.440 --> 04:28.920
And also to say a few words about Hezbollah,

04:28.920 --> 04:34.040
because the Hezbollah-Israel conflict is connected to Gaza.

04:34.040 --> 04:37.200
So that's the first conflict I want to look at.

04:37.200 --> 04:40.600
Then the second conflict I want to look at

04:41.240 --> 04:44.240
is the Iran-Israel-U.S. conflict

04:44.240 --> 04:50.240
that took place April 1st, April 14th, and April 19th.

04:51.960 --> 04:57.960
And I want to figure out what exactly happened there

04:57.960 --> 05:00.760
and what the consequences are.

05:00.760 --> 05:03.560
And of course, I'm going to do that with the Gaza war as well.

05:03.560 --> 05:06.760
So those are the two conflicts I'm going to look at.

05:06.760 --> 05:10.960
And then what I want to do in the second part of the talk

05:10.960 --> 05:14.280
is I want to talk about the consequences of all of this,

05:14.280 --> 05:18.880
the consequences of those two conflicts for Israel,

05:18.880 --> 05:22.440
for the United States, and for Iran.

05:22.440 --> 05:26.760
And my basic argument is that Israel is the big loser.

05:26.760 --> 05:30.000
Israel is in really serious trouble today,

05:30.000 --> 05:34.880
and there's little hope of getting away from that moving forward.

05:34.920 --> 05:38.280
Second, that the Americans are also losers,

05:38.280 --> 05:43.000
although they do not lose as big as Israel does.

05:43.000 --> 05:45.960
And the winners, not in any decisive way,

05:45.960 --> 05:48.680
but the winners are the Iranians.

05:48.680 --> 05:52.800
So that's the basic structure of my talk this evening.

05:53.920 --> 05:57.760
Now, let me start with what happened on October 7th

05:57.760 --> 06:00.720
and talk about the Gaza war.

06:00.720 --> 06:02.880
And just for purposes of background,

06:02.880 --> 06:05.200
for putting a framework in your head,

06:05.200 --> 06:10.040
it's very important to understand that Israel today

06:10.040 --> 06:13.280
is what I would call greater Israel.

06:13.280 --> 06:17.640
Israel controls everything between the river and the sea.

06:17.640 --> 06:22.000
And of course, that phrase is usually associated with Hamas.

06:22.000 --> 06:24.480
And what Hamas wants is to control everything

06:24.480 --> 06:27.920
between the river and the sea, just like Israel does.

06:27.920 --> 06:30.480
And the end result is that what you have today

06:30.480 --> 06:32.720
is a greater Israel.

06:32.720 --> 06:36.120
And that greater Israel includes

06:36.120 --> 06:38.080
what's called Green Line Israel.

06:38.080 --> 06:42.760
That was Israel before the 1967 war,

06:42.760 --> 06:46.960
plus Gaza, plus the West Bank.

06:46.960 --> 06:49.240
Okay, so there are those three areas

06:49.240 --> 06:51.360
that comprise greater Israel.

06:52.520 --> 06:56.040
And what's very important to understand

06:56.040 --> 06:58.320
is that inside greater Israel,

06:58.320 --> 07:03.120
there are roughly 7.3 million Palestinians

07:03.120 --> 07:07.400
and roughly 7.3 million Israeli Jews.

07:07.400 --> 07:12.040
There is rough equality between the two sides.

07:12.040 --> 07:16.440
So the question is, how does Israel think

07:16.440 --> 07:20.640
about dealing with greater Israel

07:20.640 --> 07:24.640
where you have rough equality between these two populations?

07:24.800 --> 07:28.360
And there are basically four options.

07:28.360 --> 07:33.200
One is you have a democratic greater Israel.

07:33.200 --> 07:34.520
That's not gonna happen

07:34.520 --> 07:37.160
because it would no longer be a Jewish state.

07:38.400 --> 07:41.560
Okay, because if you look at demographic patterns,

07:41.560 --> 07:43.560
the Palestinians are making more babies

07:43.560 --> 07:45.080
than the Israeli Jews.

07:45.080 --> 07:47.360
So that's not happening.

07:47.360 --> 07:50.800
Second possibility is a two-state solution.

07:50.800 --> 07:53.640
Everybody loves to talk about a two-state solution.

07:53.640 --> 07:55.040
That is not happening.

07:55.040 --> 07:57.400
Certainly after what happened on October 7th,

07:57.400 --> 07:59.960
but even before then, and I'll talk more about this,

07:59.960 --> 08:02.600
Benjamin Netanyahu and the Israeli elite

08:02.600 --> 08:07.000
has no interest in a two-state solution, okay?

08:07.000 --> 08:09.640
The third possibility is apartheid.

08:09.640 --> 08:13.560
And basically what you now have is an apartheid state.

08:13.560 --> 08:15.680
We can go into this in detail in the Q&A

08:15.680 --> 08:16.960
if you wanna do that,

08:16.960 --> 08:19.920
but if you look at Amnesty International,

08:19.920 --> 08:22.640
Human Rights Watch, and Bicellum,

08:22.680 --> 08:26.120
which is the leading human rights group in Israel,

08:26.120 --> 08:28.800
all three of those organizations

08:28.800 --> 08:31.280
have produced lengthy reports

08:31.280 --> 08:34.800
that lay out why Israel is an apartheid state.

08:36.240 --> 08:39.760
The fourth option is ethnic cleansing.

08:39.760 --> 08:43.800
And ethnic cleansing means getting rid of the Palestinians

08:43.800 --> 08:45.840
for the most part who live in Gaza

08:45.840 --> 08:47.880
and who live in the West Bank,

08:47.880 --> 08:49.880
and creating a greater Israel

08:49.880 --> 08:52.440
that is completely dominated by Israeli Jews

08:52.440 --> 08:57.360
and has very few, if any, Palestinians in its midst.

08:57.360 --> 09:00.240
So again, the four options are,

09:00.240 --> 09:04.640
number one, democratic greater Israel,

09:04.640 --> 09:06.320
number two, two-state solution.

09:06.320 --> 09:07.920
Those two are off the table.

09:07.920 --> 09:09.520
Number three, apartheid,

09:09.520 --> 09:11.440
which is basically what you have now.

09:11.440 --> 09:13.800
And number four is ethnic cleansing,

09:13.800 --> 09:17.080
where you get rid of the Palestinians, okay?

09:17.080 --> 09:19.680
Now, let's switch gears a bit

09:19.680 --> 09:22.880
and talk about what the situation looked like

09:22.880 --> 09:24.800
before October 7th,

09:26.160 --> 09:29.040
and focus mainly on Gaza.

09:29.040 --> 09:31.240
Before October 7th,

09:31.240 --> 09:33.920
the Palestinians in Gaza

09:33.920 --> 09:37.600
basically lived in a giant open-air prison.

09:37.600 --> 09:40.560
What happened was that in 2005,

09:40.560 --> 09:43.680
when Ariel Sharon was the prime minister of Israel,

09:43.680 --> 09:48.680
he decided to pull the settlers out of Gaza.

09:49.680 --> 09:51.920
As you know, there are settlers in the West Bank.

09:51.920 --> 09:56.040
Up until 2005, there were Israeli settlers in Gaza,

09:56.040 --> 09:58.160
and Sharon pulled them out.

09:58.160 --> 09:59.200
And he pulled them out

09:59.200 --> 10:01.520
because Gaza was a hornet's nest,

10:01.520 --> 10:05.040
and having settlers in there was a nightmare.

10:05.040 --> 10:07.040
And they had their hands full in the West Bank,

10:07.040 --> 10:09.240
and they wanted to focus on the West Bank.

10:09.240 --> 10:11.960
And what they did was pulled all the settlers out,

10:11.960 --> 10:14.400
and it became an open-air prison.

10:14.400 --> 10:18.320
Now, it looked up until October 7th,

10:18.360 --> 10:20.320
like Netanyahu and company

10:20.320 --> 10:25.320
were able to manage the situation inside of Gaza.

10:26.920 --> 10:31.400
Nobody thought what happened on October 7th was gonna happen.

10:31.400 --> 10:34.160
This is why the Israelis got caught with their pants down.

10:34.160 --> 10:39.160
They thought they were managing the situation very well.

10:39.280 --> 10:42.040
And what was going on there

10:42.040 --> 10:45.880
is that Netanyahu was actually very happy

10:45.880 --> 10:49.560
with the fact that Hamas was running Gaza.

10:49.560 --> 10:52.240
This is hard to believe today, but it is true.

10:52.240 --> 10:57.240
And he was making sure that Hamas was being funded

10:57.640 --> 11:02.640
and that Hamas was doing reasonably well.

11:03.080 --> 11:04.760
Now, why is that the case?

11:04.760 --> 11:07.320
Because Netanyahu is adamantly opposed

11:07.320 --> 11:09.160
to a two-state solution.

11:09.160 --> 11:13.920
And Mahmoud Abbas, who runs the Palestinian Authority

11:13.960 --> 11:18.560
in the West Bank, is in favor of a two-state solution.

11:18.560 --> 11:21.800
So from Sharon's point of view, not Sharon,

11:21.800 --> 11:23.640
from Netanyahu's point of view,

11:23.640 --> 11:25.880
would have been true from Sharon's point of view as well,

11:25.880 --> 11:27.360
as if he hadn't passed away,

11:28.560 --> 11:32.680
Abbas is a threat because Abbas wants a two-state solution.

11:34.320 --> 11:39.320
So what Netanyahu has done is supported Hamas

11:39.640 --> 11:43.040
because we all know Hamas does not want a two-state solution.

11:43.080 --> 11:48.080
And he's playing off Hamas against the PLO

11:48.960 --> 11:51.880
in the West Bank.

11:51.880 --> 11:53.800
And it looks like it works.

11:53.800 --> 11:56.160
And by the way, every once in a while,

11:56.160 --> 11:59.800
every couple of years, the Israelis mow the lawn,

11:59.800 --> 12:03.520
which means they precipitate a conflict with the Palestinians,

12:03.520 --> 12:05.280
they go in there, they kill hundreds,

12:05.280 --> 12:07.120
if not thousands of Palestinians,

12:07.120 --> 12:10.840
destroy some buildings and send them a very clear message

12:10.880 --> 12:13.840
that, you know, we're in charge

12:13.840 --> 12:16.160
and we want you to understand

12:16.160 --> 12:19.760
that you have to remain in this open-air prison.

12:19.760 --> 12:21.840
So that's the basic situation that exists.

12:21.840 --> 12:25.320
It looks like Netanyahu is managing the situation.

12:25.320 --> 12:27.680
And almost everybody thinks that,

12:27.680 --> 12:29.400
which is again, is why they get caught

12:29.400 --> 12:32.520
with their pants down on October 7th.

12:32.520 --> 12:36.120
But again, what happens on October 7th

12:36.120 --> 12:41.120
is that Hamas attacks into Israel.

12:41.480 --> 12:46.480
And I think it's fair to say, achieves a spectacular success.

12:46.640 --> 12:49.800
I think the evidence is that Hamas was surprised

12:49.800 --> 12:52.040
by how successful they were.

12:53.600 --> 12:57.600
And anyway, they eventually leave Israel

12:57.600 --> 13:01.720
and the Israelis consolidate the situation

13:01.720 --> 13:04.000
inside of their borders.

13:04.920 --> 13:09.920
And then they eventually go on the offensive against Hamas.

13:11.560 --> 13:14.920
And that offensive is now taking place.

13:14.920 --> 13:18.000
Okay, now what we wanna ask ourselves

13:18.000 --> 13:22.080
is what exactly are Israel's goals here?

13:22.080 --> 13:23.600
This is very important to understand

13:23.600 --> 13:25.640
what Israel is trying to do.

13:25.640 --> 13:28.240
Now, if you read the mainstream media in the West,

13:28.240 --> 13:29.920
and this includes Australia,

13:29.920 --> 13:33.960
what people talk about is that Israel is interested

13:34.440 --> 13:37.000
in number one, defeating Hamas.

13:37.000 --> 13:39.840
And here we're talking about decisively defeating Hamas

13:39.840 --> 13:41.440
and eliminating Hamas.

13:41.440 --> 13:43.520
And you can understand why from Israel's point of view

13:43.520 --> 13:45.280
that makes sense.

13:45.280 --> 13:48.880
Second goal is to get the hostages back.

13:48.880 --> 13:53.400
As you all know, Hamas took about 240 hostages.

13:53.400 --> 13:55.440
And what the Israelis obviously wanna do

13:55.440 --> 13:57.360
is get those hostages back.

13:57.360 --> 13:59.760
So there's sort of two principal goals here.

13:59.800 --> 14:04.800
Defeat Hamas decisively and get back the hostages.

14:04.920 --> 14:09.400
What's not discussed in the Western media is the real goal.

14:09.400 --> 14:13.400
And the real goal is to ethnically cleanse Gaza.

14:13.400 --> 14:16.280
And the reason they wanna ethnically cleanse Gaza

14:16.280 --> 14:19.680
is because number one,

14:20.840 --> 14:24.480
that's the way you get out of apartheid.

14:24.480 --> 14:28.240
You all understand Israel is an apartheid state.

14:28.240 --> 14:33.240
And the only way you get out of that situation is you cleanse.

14:35.760 --> 14:38.800
Furthermore, it's the only way you defeat Hamas.

14:38.800 --> 14:40.120
I'll talk more about this.

14:40.120 --> 14:42.120
It's quite clear that the Israelis

14:42.120 --> 14:44.960
are not gonna defeat Hamas, right?

14:44.960 --> 14:48.080
And I can't believe they thought they would defeat Hamas

14:48.080 --> 14:49.400
before they went in there.

14:49.400 --> 14:51.600
They're too smart for that.

14:53.080 --> 14:55.680
But if you cleanse Gaza

14:55.680 --> 14:57.920
and you drive all the Palestinians out,

14:57.920 --> 14:59.760
you drive Hamas out.

14:59.760 --> 15:02.760
So you solve two of the principal problems you face

15:02.760 --> 15:04.040
with ethnic cleansing.

15:05.400 --> 15:07.240
You solve the apartheid problem

15:08.520 --> 15:10.960
and you solve the Hamas problem.

15:10.960 --> 15:12.200
Now you're probably saying to yourself,

15:12.200 --> 15:14.560
Israel wouldn't do anything like this.

15:16.840 --> 15:17.800
Just a couple of points.

15:17.800 --> 15:20.280
First of all, to create the state of Israel,

15:20.280 --> 15:23.320
to begin with, you had to do massive ethnic cleansing.

15:23.320 --> 15:27.000
In 1948 and in 1967,

15:27.000 --> 15:31.760
the Israelis cleansed huge portions

15:31.760 --> 15:34.440
of what is today greater Israel.

15:34.440 --> 15:36.480
And the idea that they wouldn't do this,

15:36.480 --> 15:40.680
if you read all sorts of Israeli media,

15:40.680 --> 15:43.920
they talk about ethnic cleansing all the time.

15:43.920 --> 15:46.320
And it makes perfect sense if you think about it.

15:47.560 --> 15:51.240
Final point I'd make to you is one of the criticisms

15:51.240 --> 15:53.000
that I'll talk more about this

15:53.000 --> 15:55.800
of what the Israelis and especially Benjamin Netanyahu

15:56.000 --> 15:57.520
are doing in Gaza,

15:57.520 --> 16:00.320
is they have not come up with a plan

16:01.360 --> 16:05.600
for what Gaza is going to look like

16:05.600 --> 16:07.480
after the shooting stops.

16:07.480 --> 16:11.000
In other words, what's the political solution here

16:11.000 --> 16:13.240
once the shooting stops?

16:13.240 --> 16:17.520
And Israeli military commanders, IDF military commanders

16:17.520 --> 16:19.560
are constantly complaining these days

16:19.560 --> 16:22.400
that Netanyahu doesn't give them any sense

16:22.400 --> 16:26.800
of what the final political settlement's gonna look like

16:26.800 --> 16:28.200
so they can deal with Hamas

16:28.200 --> 16:29.400
and deal with the Palestinians

16:29.400 --> 16:33.080
with some thought in mind about what the end game is here.

16:33.080 --> 16:35.520
For the reason there's no end game,

16:35.520 --> 16:37.000
the reason they're not talking about

16:37.000 --> 16:39.520
how they're going to administer

16:39.520 --> 16:41.800
a Palestinian-dominated Gaza

16:41.800 --> 16:44.600
is because they want the Palestinians out.

16:44.600 --> 16:46.880
They wanna ethically cleanse Gaza.

16:47.800 --> 16:50.440
And then that brings us to the question,

16:50.440 --> 16:52.440
how do you do this, right?

16:52.440 --> 16:54.960
How do you get the Palestinians out?

16:54.960 --> 16:58.160
Well, first of all,

16:59.160 --> 17:03.160
they definitely went after Hamas to start with.

17:03.440 --> 17:06.640
That was the purely military side of the story.

17:06.640 --> 17:08.120
They went after Hamas.

17:09.120 --> 17:12.240
But to make ethnic cleansing work,

17:12.240 --> 17:15.280
you have to number one,

17:15.280 --> 17:17.600
you have to number one,

17:17.600 --> 17:21.440
kill significant numbers of people,

17:21.440 --> 17:25.880
of Palestinians who are basically innocent Palestinians,

17:25.880 --> 17:27.480
not Hamas.

17:27.480 --> 17:29.400
You have to kill large numbers of them

17:29.400 --> 17:31.440
and you have to give them a powerful incentive

17:31.440 --> 17:33.560
by killing them to drive them out.

17:34.480 --> 17:39.480
Number two, you have to make the place unlivable.

17:40.120 --> 17:41.840
And that's what they're doing.

17:41.840 --> 17:45.240
I mean, they're not just killing people.

17:45.240 --> 17:48.640
They're making Gaza unlivable.

17:48.640 --> 17:51.840
I could go through this in detail in the Q and A

17:51.840 --> 17:54.320
if people wanna hear the story.

17:54.320 --> 17:57.920
But it is, as many people say,

17:57.920 --> 18:00.120
especially the UN people who are there,

18:00.120 --> 18:01.560
the place is unlivable.

18:01.560 --> 18:02.920
And the reason it's unlivable

