27% are not sure.

37:27.720 --> 37:32.520
And then 15% do not believe Israel is committing genocide.

37:32.520 --> 37:34.400
This is quite remarkable.

37:34.400 --> 37:37.800
When I think about how I thought about Israel

37:37.800 --> 37:41.160
and virtually everybody I knew thought about Israel

37:41.160 --> 37:44.200
when I was a young boy and I was a young man

37:44.280 --> 37:48.800
and how virtually everybody I know now thinks about Israel,

37:49.680 --> 37:52.920
a fundamental transformation has taken place.

37:52.920 --> 37:54.960
It's really quite remarkable.

37:54.960 --> 37:56.720
And the idea that the Jewish state

37:56.720 --> 37:59.400
is being accused of genocide,

37:59.400 --> 38:01.000
it's really quite remarkable.

38:02.000 --> 38:04.120
This is a sign of big trouble

38:04.120 --> 38:08.120
and the use of the apartheid label is used increasingly.

38:08.120 --> 38:10.160
And this is not gonna change

38:10.160 --> 38:13.400
because the situation in Gaza is not gonna get any better.

38:13.400 --> 38:15.760
That was one of the points I'm trying to get through to you.

38:15.760 --> 38:18.480
There is no solution on the horizon here.

38:18.480 --> 38:21.040
If anybody asked me in the question and answer period,

38:21.040 --> 38:23.280
what would I do to fix this problem?

38:23.280 --> 38:25.000
I could tell you what the answer is now.

38:25.000 --> 38:26.320
I have no idea.

38:27.560 --> 38:29.160
Let's be very clear on this.

38:29.160 --> 38:31.120
Categorically depressing.

38:31.120 --> 38:35.360
But anyway, I think that from Israel's point of view,

38:35.360 --> 38:39.520
what's happened to its reputation is disastrous

38:39.520 --> 38:42.840
and I don't think it's gonna get any better over time.

38:42.840 --> 38:45.760
So this is why these four reasons,

38:45.760 --> 38:50.440
number one, the fact they're stuck in Gaza once more.

38:50.440 --> 38:53.680
Number two, the fact that their deterrence has been weakened

38:53.680 --> 38:55.960
because they don't have escalation dominance.

38:55.960 --> 39:00.240
Number three, the fact that they're surrounded by adversaries

39:00.240 --> 39:03.920
who loathe them, would like to destroy them

39:03.920 --> 39:08.600
and who have increasing numbers of missiles and drones

39:08.600 --> 39:12.120
that can cause them lots of trouble is bad news.

39:12.160 --> 39:16.000
And number four, the pariah state argument.

39:16.000 --> 39:18.040
Now let me conclude by talking briefly

39:18.040 --> 39:20.640
about the United States and talking about Iran.

39:21.800 --> 39:24.520
The United States is also a big loser here.

39:25.960 --> 39:28.280
First of all, it's in our interest

39:28.280 --> 39:30.600
to have peace in the Middle East.

39:30.600 --> 39:33.200
First of all, we've been fighting so many wars.

39:33.200 --> 39:36.280
The American public is just sick of all these wars.

39:36.280 --> 39:39.720
The last thing we want are more wars in the Middle East.

39:39.720 --> 39:41.440
Oh my God, a war against Iran.

39:41.440 --> 39:43.840
This is the last thing people want, right?

39:43.840 --> 39:45.120
We want peace.

39:45.120 --> 39:47.320
Furthermore, we need a peaceful Middle East

39:47.320 --> 39:50.560
so we can pivot to East Asia, right?

39:50.560 --> 39:52.400
From the American point of view,

39:52.400 --> 39:55.120
the most serious threat on the planet is China.

39:55.120 --> 39:57.360
The United States has to contain China.

39:57.360 --> 39:59.000
We have to pivot to Asia.

39:59.000 --> 40:02.240
We can't pivot to Asia because we're pinned down in Ukraine

40:02.240 --> 40:06.600
and now we're pinned down in the Middle East.

40:06.600 --> 40:08.400
This is not good.

40:08.400 --> 40:13.120
We want for sure to settle this one, right?

40:13.120 --> 40:17.640
To have a situation like the one that existed

40:17.640 --> 40:19.880
before October 7th.

40:19.880 --> 40:21.800
Remember Jake Sullivan said a few weeks

40:21.800 --> 40:24.640
before October 7th, we haven't seen the Middle East

40:24.640 --> 40:26.480
this peaceful for a long time

40:26.480 --> 40:28.640
and he was very happy about that

40:28.640 --> 40:31.960
and it made perfect sense from an American point of view.

40:31.960 --> 40:35.640
But that went away very quickly on October 7th.

40:35.640 --> 40:37.200
So we want peace.

40:37.200 --> 40:42.200
Second point is we also care greatly

40:42.320 --> 40:45.200
about having friendly relations

40:45.200 --> 40:49.000
with as many states in the Middle East as possible.

40:49.000 --> 40:50.760
Why is that the case?

40:50.760 --> 40:54.480
The Russians are already there, number one,

40:54.480 --> 40:57.800
and two, the Chinese are beginning to move in.

40:57.800 --> 40:59.800
For all the older dogs,

40:59.800 --> 41:02.880
I noticed there are a number of older dogs in the audience.

41:02.880 --> 41:06.600
We all remember back in the day, right?

41:06.600 --> 41:11.600
When the US and the Soviet Union competed in the Middle East.

41:12.920 --> 41:16.720
Well, what you're gonna see moving forward

41:16.720 --> 41:19.200
is not just the United States and Russia,

41:19.200 --> 41:22.040
but the United States, Russia and China

41:22.040 --> 41:24.240
competing in the Middle East.

41:24.240 --> 41:26.160
The Chinese are building a blue water navy

41:26.160 --> 41:29.000
to project power into the Gulf, number one.

41:29.000 --> 41:32.760
Number two, they depend heavily on oil

41:32.760 --> 41:35.000
and therefore they're doing everything they can

41:35.000 --> 41:36.680
to have good relations with Iran,

41:36.680 --> 41:39.040
good relations with Saudi Arabia.

41:39.040 --> 41:42.800
And we are very worried about this.

41:42.800 --> 41:46.840
The United States doesn't want bad relations

41:46.840 --> 41:48.160
with countries in the Middle East

41:48.160 --> 41:51.880
that drive them into the arms of the Chinese and the Russians.

41:51.880 --> 41:53.400
And you see a lot of that happening.

41:53.400 --> 41:56.200
By the way, you all know about the Abraham Accords.

41:56.200 --> 42:00.280
The Abraham Accords was where the United States

42:00.280 --> 42:04.760
was recently trying to get Israel, Saudi Arabia,

42:04.760 --> 42:10.000
and the United States all together in a sort of quasi-alliance.

42:10.000 --> 42:11.800
This is all gone by the boards now

42:11.800 --> 42:14.320
because of what's happening in Gaza, right?

42:14.320 --> 42:15.480
This is not in our interest.

42:15.480 --> 42:17.200
It's certainly not in Israel's interest

42:17.200 --> 42:21.040
and it's certainly not in Saudi's interest at all, either.

42:21.040 --> 42:25.320
So you see the problem that we have here,

42:25.320 --> 42:29.800
just one other problem, and this applies to the Israelis as well,

42:29.800 --> 42:31.320
is the nuclear issue.

42:31.320 --> 42:36.320
You all understand Iran is hopskipping a jump away

42:36.320 --> 42:39.240
from developing nuclear weapons

42:39.240 --> 42:42.680
because we, with pressure from the Israelis,

42:42.680 --> 42:47.120
we the Americans, pulled out of the JCPOA.

42:47.120 --> 42:48.760
That was the nuclear agreement

42:48.760 --> 42:53.640
that the Obama administration crafted with Iran.

42:53.640 --> 42:59.280
The Iranians are now enriching uranium up to 60%.

42:59.280 --> 43:03.560
And you have to enrich uranium up to 90%

43:03.560 --> 43:11.120
to have it capable of being turned into a bomb.

43:11.120 --> 43:14.600
And it's very easy to get from 60% to 90%.

43:14.600 --> 43:17.680
My guess is, and just from reading the literature,

43:17.680 --> 43:21.320
that Iran could have enough fissile material

43:21.320 --> 43:24.720
for three bombs in about six weeks.

43:24.720 --> 43:25.720
That's not a bomb.

43:25.720 --> 43:27.240
That's just a fissile material.

43:27.240 --> 43:29.240
I think it would take probably about six months

43:29.240 --> 43:30.920
to build three bombs,

43:30.920 --> 43:34.680
and then they'd have to develop the delivery capability.

43:34.680 --> 43:37.280
So it's not like they're going to develop a bomb

43:37.280 --> 43:38.680
in a month or two's time.

43:38.680 --> 43:42.800
That's not going to happen, but they're not that far away.

43:42.800 --> 43:47.240
And what happens when you bomb their embassy

43:47.240 --> 43:51.280
and then you get in a tit for tat,

43:51.280 --> 43:55.560
fight with them on April 14th and April 19th

43:55.600 --> 43:58.840
is you give them an incentive to get nuclear weapons.

43:58.840 --> 44:01.400
And you can see signs of that.

44:01.400 --> 44:03.400
You can see signs of the Iranians

44:03.400 --> 44:05.600
talking about getting nuclear weapons.

44:05.600 --> 44:08.520
So one of the principal problems

44:08.520 --> 44:10.240
that the Israelis and the Americans face

44:10.240 --> 44:14.120
as a result of what happened between April 1st and April 19th

44:14.120 --> 44:18.080
is we've incentivized the Iranians to get nuclear weapons.

44:18.080 --> 44:19.600
Not that they'll go through with it,

44:19.600 --> 44:22.520
but we've given them powerful incentive to do that,

44:22.520 --> 44:25.120
and they have the capability

44:25.120 --> 44:28.640
because they can enrich uranium up to 90%

44:28.640 --> 44:30.960
and then produce bombs.

44:30.960 --> 44:34.640
Just say a few words in conclusion, Tom, about Iran.

44:34.640 --> 44:37.040
As I said to you before, I think Iran is the winner.

44:37.040 --> 44:38.440
I think America's the loser.

44:38.440 --> 44:41.040
I think Israel is the biggest loser.

44:41.040 --> 44:45.720
But I think that the Iranians are the winners so far.

44:45.720 --> 44:49.480
And this is not to say that they have really come out

44:49.480 --> 44:53.200
of this smelling like a rose, as my mother used to say.

44:53.200 --> 44:54.720
I don't want to go that far.

44:54.720 --> 44:58.920
But on balance, I think they've done quite well for themselves.

44:58.920 --> 45:03.280
First of all, they have been able, except for April 14th,

45:03.280 --> 45:06.080
to remain on the sidelines.

45:06.080 --> 45:09.440
And they are using their proxies in the region

45:09.440 --> 45:11.640
or they're working with their proxies.

45:11.640 --> 45:14.720
That's a better way to put it, to great effect.

45:14.720 --> 45:18.960
Because as you know, the Iranians are allied with Hamas.

45:18.960 --> 45:20.680
They're allied with Hezbollah.

45:20.680 --> 45:22.400
They're allied with the Houthis.

45:22.480 --> 45:27.480
And they're allied with these militias inside of Iraq and Syria

45:27.480 --> 45:30.600
that have their gun sights not only on the United States,

45:30.600 --> 45:34.080
but on Israel as well.

45:34.080 --> 45:39.120
So they have been able to stay out of the fight,

45:39.120 --> 45:45.240
yet see their proxies do very well in this conflict

45:45.240 --> 45:52.080
with both the United States and Israel.

45:52.080 --> 45:54.880
Another point that you want to keep in mind

45:54.880 --> 45:59.360
is that Iran, as a result of all this,

45:59.360 --> 46:03.160
now has very close relations with Russia and China.

46:03.160 --> 46:06.200
What we're doing, what the United States is doing,

46:06.200 --> 46:09.520
is we're driving the Iranians, the Russians, the Chinese,

46:09.520 --> 46:13.440
and the North Koreans together.

46:13.440 --> 46:17.200
This makes it harder for us to isolate Iran.

46:17.200 --> 46:21.040
And if Iran starts to go down the nuclear road, nuclear weapons

46:21.400 --> 46:24.200
road, and we want to put pressure on the Iranians,

46:24.200 --> 46:26.000
it's not clear the Chinese and the Russians

46:26.000 --> 46:27.600
are going to help us very much.

46:27.600 --> 46:30.880
We need the Chinese and the Russians to help us.

46:30.880 --> 46:33.280
But anyway, the Iranians feel like they're

46:33.280 --> 46:36.760
in quite a good situation, because the United States

46:36.760 --> 46:39.240
and the Israelis have not been able to do anything

46:39.240 --> 46:41.080
to really harm them.

46:41.080 --> 46:44.000
In fact, Iran got away with whacking Israel.

46:44.000 --> 46:46.640
This is the first time that Iran has ever

46:46.640 --> 46:50.840
been able to launch missiles and drones from its own territory,

46:50.840 --> 46:54.600
hit Israel, and Israel barely retaliated.

46:54.600 --> 46:57.760
Iranians are probably feeling good about that, as they should.

47:00.600 --> 47:04.080
And then the final point is the sanctions against Iran

47:04.080 --> 47:06.800
are not working the way they once were.

47:06.800 --> 47:08.600
They have weakened.

47:08.600 --> 47:13.200
So if you look overall at what's happened to the Iranians

47:13.200 --> 47:15.920
and what's happening to the Americans,

47:15.920 --> 47:19.160
and especially what's happening to the Israelis,

47:19.240 --> 47:23.240
you see that the situation after October 7th

47:23.240 --> 47:26.560
is fundamentally different than the situation

47:26.560 --> 47:29.160
before October 7th.

47:29.160 --> 47:32.120
Just in the case of the Israelis, before October 7th,

47:32.120 --> 47:34.520
it looked like they were in the cat bird seat.

47:34.520 --> 47:38.720
They were managing very well in their own opinion

47:38.720 --> 47:40.440
the situation in Gaza.

47:40.440 --> 47:41.920
And by the way, I want to be clear here.

47:41.920 --> 47:44.840
I thought they were doing an excellent job

47:44.840 --> 47:47.040
of managing the problem in Gaza.

47:47.040 --> 47:49.160
I thought they had things under control.

47:49.160 --> 47:52.920
I was shocked by what happened on October 7th.

47:52.920 --> 47:56.160
But once October 7th happened, and as we've watched

47:56.160 --> 47:58.720
these two conflicts play themselves out,

47:58.720 --> 48:03.720
one, the war in Gaza, and how that's linked to Hezbollah,

48:04.000 --> 48:06.240
you don't want to forget, and then two,

48:06.240 --> 48:10.440
the Iran-Israel-United States exchange

48:10.440 --> 48:13.040
between April 1st and April 19th.

48:13.040 --> 48:16.080
It's quite clear that the world has changed

48:16.080 --> 48:19.960
in ways that are not good for either Israel

48:19.960 --> 48:21.520
or the United States.

48:21.520 --> 48:23.360
Thank you.

48:23.360 --> 48:24.320
Welcome back to CIS.

48:24.320 --> 48:26.640
It's great to have you back.

48:26.640 --> 48:28.480
Notwithstanding all those points you made

48:28.480 --> 48:32.880
about escalation dominance and the fact that the Israelis

48:32.880 --> 48:37.360
are now bogged down in Gaza, aren't you overstating

48:37.360 --> 48:40.200
your point about Israel's grim security outlook?

48:40.200 --> 48:42.360
After all, it's not declared,

48:42.360 --> 48:44.840
but they do have nuclear weapons.

48:44.840 --> 48:47.080
And as a foreign policy realist,

48:47.080 --> 48:49.480
you would surely concede that nuclear weapons

48:49.480 --> 48:52.840
are the ultimate deterrent to a foreign attack.

48:52.840 --> 48:54.480
So are you being overly gloomy

48:54.480 --> 48:56.680
about Israel's security outlook?

48:58.720 --> 49:01.320
