49:01.320 --> 49:05.120
that nuclear weapons are the ultimate deterrent.

49:05.120 --> 49:09.360
And I don't think any country with nuclear weapons

49:09.400 --> 49:12.320
is gonna disappear from the planet

49:12.320 --> 49:15.560
because another country attacks it.

49:15.560 --> 49:18.680
I think that no country would try to inflict

49:18.680 --> 49:23.680
a decisive defeat on Israel because it has nuclear weapons.

49:28.280 --> 49:33.280
But the problem is that Israel has an internal problem.

49:34.280 --> 49:38.280
See, Tom's point about nuclear weapons applies

49:38.280 --> 49:42.280
if you're talking about Iran hitting Israel.

49:42.280 --> 49:46.280
It's an interstate problem, okay?

49:46.280 --> 49:51.280
But Hamas is not another country.

49:51.280 --> 49:55.280
Hamas is inside greater Israel.

49:55.280 --> 50:00.280
What Hamas is doing is executing a rebellion

50:03.280 --> 50:08.280
or executing an insurrection.

50:08.320 --> 50:11.920
And nuclear weapons don't do anything for you

50:11.920 --> 50:13.680
in that regard.

50:13.680 --> 50:15.720
To take this a step further,

50:15.720 --> 50:19.160
we've talked a little bit just briefly about South Africa

50:19.160 --> 50:22.840
and the fact that South Africa was an apartheid state.

50:22.840 --> 50:25.440
And basically that state that existed,

50:25.440 --> 50:28.360
apartheid South Africa, disappeared.

50:28.360 --> 50:30.600
That state had nuclear weapons.

50:30.600 --> 50:32.600
South Africa had nuclear weapons.

50:32.720 --> 50:34.240
And what you wanna understand,

50:34.240 --> 50:37.000
and this is very important in the Israeli context,

50:37.000 --> 50:41.000
is that what's happening inside your society,

50:41.000 --> 50:46.000
inside your body politic matters enormously.

50:46.160 --> 50:49.920
And nuclear weapons can't do much to protect you.

50:49.920 --> 50:52.040
You see what I'm saying?

50:52.040 --> 50:55.000
But I don't wanna take away from his basic point

50:55.000 --> 50:57.840
that nuclear weapons do provide deterrence

50:57.840 --> 51:00.720
against Iran getting nuclear weapons or...

51:01.680 --> 51:04.080
Well, I mean, many scholars would still argue

51:04.080 --> 51:06.600
that the security outlook for Israel

51:06.600 --> 51:08.400
is not as grim as you point out,

51:08.400 --> 51:10.840
not just because of their access to nuclear weapons.

51:10.840 --> 51:11.680
Let me put this to you.

51:11.680 --> 51:14.640
This is Fareed Zakaria, a CNN host

51:14.640 --> 51:16.760
who's also a columnist at the Washington Post.

51:16.760 --> 51:18.760
Now, admittedly, he said this before October 7,

51:18.760 --> 51:19.680
but let me put this to you.

51:19.680 --> 51:21.400
This is what he says.

51:21.400 --> 51:25.000
First, there is the disappearance of the Arab threat.

51:25.000 --> 51:27.400
From its first day in existence,

51:27.440 --> 51:31.640
Israel has faced the danger of extinction by Arab armies.

51:31.640 --> 51:34.160
This is the threat against which the Jewish state

51:34.160 --> 51:39.080
has planned, armed and trade for most of its national life.

51:39.080 --> 51:41.080
Today, that threat is gone.

51:41.080 --> 51:43.840
Second, the armies from Israel's main strategic

51:43.840 --> 51:47.640
adversaries, Iraq, Syria, Egypt, historically,

51:47.640 --> 51:50.680
they're in disarray while the Israeli armed forces

51:50.680 --> 51:52.760
have become the region's superpower

51:52.760 --> 51:54.560
in a league ahead of the rest.

51:54.560 --> 51:56.720
How would you respond to Fareed Zakaria?

51:56.720 --> 52:03.840
He's right in that sense that those traditional adversaries

52:03.840 --> 52:06.160
have effectively disappeared.

52:06.160 --> 52:12.200
When I was young and the 1956 war took place, the 1967 war

52:12.200 --> 52:16.160
took place, the 1973 war took place,

52:16.160 --> 52:18.920
these were all conflicts that involved Israel

52:18.920 --> 52:21.120
up against Arab states.

52:21.120 --> 52:26.320
And by the way, in 1948, when Israel got its independence,

52:26.320 --> 52:31.400
May 14, 1948, yesterday was Israeli Independence Day.

52:31.400 --> 52:33.480
But it's an anniversary.

52:33.480 --> 52:37.160
Yeah, but there's no question that the Israelis fought wars

52:37.160 --> 52:39.960
in 1948 against.

52:39.960 --> 52:41.240
That's his point.

52:41.240 --> 52:43.360
But that's not the threat anymore.

52:43.360 --> 52:46.480
There's a whole new set of threats called Hamas,

52:46.480 --> 52:50.440
called Hezbollah, called the Houthis.

52:50.440 --> 52:53.720
But aren't we seeing a broader trend in the Middle East

52:53.720 --> 52:56.320
between the Iranian-backed Shia proxies

52:56.320 --> 53:01.480
that you just mentioned, Hezbollah and the Houthi rebels,

53:01.480 --> 53:05.160
versus Saudi Arabia and the Sunni Gulf states?

53:05.160 --> 53:06.440
Isn't that the broader issue?

53:06.440 --> 53:09.640
And doesn't that, to the extent that is true, help Israel?

53:09.640 --> 53:11.600
Because you've got a civil war, essentially,

53:11.600 --> 53:13.800
in the Muslim community in the Arab world.

53:13.800 --> 53:18.400
How does it help Israel solve the Gaza problem?

53:18.400 --> 53:21.840
Explain to me how that helps Israel solve the Gaza problem.

53:21.840 --> 53:23.800
And while you're at it, explain to me

53:23.800 --> 53:28.600
how it helps solve the missile problem that Hezbollah, Hamas,

53:28.600 --> 53:32.560
and the Houthis, and Iran present to Israel.

