54:47.120 --> 54:48.360
That's one point.

54:48.360 --> 54:53.040
The second point is the Palestinians in Israel

54:53.040 --> 54:55.520
do not have equal rights.

54:55.520 --> 54:57.680
There's no question they can vote,

54:57.680 --> 54:59.520
but they don't have equal rights.

54:59.520 --> 55:02.240
That's why I always argue that Israel

55:02.240 --> 55:04.840
is not a liberal democracy.

55:04.840 --> 55:08.440
If you want to argue Israel is a democracy,

55:08.440 --> 55:09.680
you can make that argument.

55:09.680 --> 55:12.760
I would even fight with you there because of the West Bank

55:12.760 --> 55:13.280
in Gaza.

55:13.280 --> 55:17.440
But let me say I'll give you that, that it is a democracy.

55:17.440 --> 55:19.480
You can't make the argument that Israel

55:19.480 --> 55:24.160
is a liberal democracy because the Palestinians don't

55:24.160 --> 55:28.280
have equal rights inside Green Line Israel.

55:28.280 --> 55:30.880
This is the principal reason, in my opinion,

55:30.880 --> 55:33.760
that Israel does not have a constitution.

55:33.760 --> 55:36.040
They've moved in that direction a couple of times,

55:36.040 --> 55:38.480
but they can't go too far down that road

55:38.480 --> 55:41.400
because they don't want equal rights.

55:41.400 --> 55:45.400
They want a Jewish state, not a state

55:45.400 --> 55:49.440
where Palestinians and Jews are equal in number

55:49.440 --> 55:51.080
and have equal rights.

55:51.080 --> 55:53.400
OK, but your critics, and they're not just Jewish leaders,

55:53.400 --> 55:54.920
a lot of people in this room, presumably,

55:54.920 --> 55:58.080
would say it's a stretch to compare Israel today

55:58.080 --> 56:02.000
to the old, racist South Africa of the SDU.

56:02.000 --> 56:04.560
And this is the late Les Gilb, someone

56:04.560 --> 56:07.200
you knew, the former president of the New York

56:07.200 --> 56:09.120
Base Council on Foreign Relations,

56:09.120 --> 56:11.680
quote, the US is helping to protect

56:11.680 --> 56:13.760
one of the few nations in the world

56:13.800 --> 56:17.520
that share American values and interests, a true democracy.

56:17.520 --> 56:19.480
And this is Richard Cohen, a longtime columnist

56:19.480 --> 56:21.600
of The Washington Post.

56:21.600 --> 56:24.840
The Israel of today and the South Africa of yesterday

56:24.840 --> 56:26.760
have almost nothing in common.

56:26.760 --> 56:30.080
In South Africa, the minority white population

56:30.080 --> 56:33.640
harshly ruled the majority black population.

56:33.640 --> 56:35.880
Non-whites were denied civil rights.

56:35.880 --> 56:39.640
And in 1958, they were even deprived of citizenship.

56:39.640 --> 56:42.320
Cohen goes on to say, in contrast,

56:42.320 --> 56:45.280
Israeli Arabs, about one-fifth of the country,

56:45.280 --> 56:49.800
have the same civil and political rights as Israeli Jews.

56:49.800 --> 56:52.880
Arabs sit in the Knesset and serve in the military,

56:52.880 --> 56:55.080
although most are exempt from the draft.

56:55.080 --> 56:58.000
And Cohen concludes, whatever this is,

56:58.000 --> 57:00.640
and it looks suspiciously like a liberal democracy,

57:00.640 --> 57:02.240
it cannot be apartheid.

57:02.240 --> 57:05.320
Again, your response to the likes of Les Gilb and Richard Cohen.

57:05.320 --> 57:07.560
Just very quickly, they don't have equal rights.

57:07.560 --> 57:10.840
This is the Palestinians who live inside Green Line Israel.

57:10.840 --> 57:14.320
They simply don't have equal rights.

57:14.320 --> 57:16.880
And what about the Palestinians in Gaza

57:16.880 --> 57:18.640
and the Palestinians in the West Bank?

57:18.640 --> 57:21.600
This is all part of Greater Israel.

57:21.600 --> 57:25.200
But let me make a couple of points in addition to that.

57:25.200 --> 57:28.400
First of all, whether Israel is an apartheid state

57:28.400 --> 57:31.800
is not based on any comparison with South Africa.

57:31.800 --> 57:35.800
You have to come up with what is a definition of apartheid.

57:35.800 --> 57:39.000
And then you have to look at what's happening inside of Israel

57:39.040 --> 57:42.200
and see whether it meets that definition.

57:42.200 --> 57:44.000
There's no question that there are differences,

57:44.000 --> 57:45.600
and I'll get to this in a second,

57:45.600 --> 57:49.840
between apartheid in South Africa and apartheid in Israel.

57:49.840 --> 57:51.160
But the question is,

57:51.160 --> 57:55.200
what are the general characteristics of an apartheid regime

57:55.200 --> 57:58.560
and does Israel fill the bill?

57:58.560 --> 58:02.680
Now, as I told you before, if you have any doubts about this,

58:02.680 --> 58:06.760
there are huge reports written by Human Rights Watch,

58:06.760 --> 58:08.800
Amnesty International and Bet-Salon,

58:08.800 --> 58:12.640
which is the leading human rights group inside of Israel,

58:12.640 --> 58:17.640
laying out the case as to why Israel is an apartheid state.

58:18.440 --> 58:23.440
And I think those three reports make a very powerful case.

58:24.280 --> 58:29.280
My final point to you is there are a number

58:30.760 --> 58:35.760
of South Africans who lived under apartheid in South Africa,

58:36.600 --> 58:41.600
including South African Jews and including Bishop Tutu,

58:44.160 --> 58:49.160
who make the argument that the apartheid system in Israel

58:49.880 --> 58:54.880
is worse than the apartheid system in South Africa.

58:55.560 --> 58:58.600
Let's turn to Rafa, the Southern city in Gaza.

58:58.600 --> 59:00.960
Now, the Israeli leadership seems to believe

59:00.960 --> 59:04.120
that a full-scale ground military invasion

59:05.120 --> 59:08.000
of Rafa will finish the job of eliminating Hamas.

59:08.000 --> 59:10.160
You've said that that's not realistic.

59:10.160 --> 59:14.080
Now, your critics would say that with its gleeful mutilations,

59:14.080 --> 59:17.720
its rampages, its rapes and beheadings,

59:17.720 --> 59:22.720
its baby killing on October 7, Hamas needs crushing.

59:23.080 --> 59:26.920
And if Hamas keeps control of Rafa and the people, it wins.

59:27.920 --> 59:32.920
The Israelis may believe that Hamas needs to be crushed.

59:33.680 --> 59:37.320
And you can understand, given what happened on October 7,

59:37.320 --> 59:41.800
why they feel that way, they're not going to crush Hamas.

59:41.800 --> 59:45.480
And if you read the newspapers carefully every day,

59:45.480 --> 59:49.160
you will see that Hamas has come back to life

59:49.160 --> 59:54.160
in northern Gaza and the Israelis have now sent military forces

59:54.160 --> 59:58.160
into northern Gaza to deal with Hamas.

59:58.160 --> 01:00:02.160
The New York Times and the Wall Street Journal today

01:00:02.160 --> 01:00:06.160
have articles dealing with the fact that Hamas

01:00:06.160 --> 01:00:09.160
is almost impossible to defeat.

01:00:09.160 --> 01:00:11.160
They're just not going to defeat them.

01:00:11.160 --> 01:00:15.160
This is why I said to you, ethnic cleansing is so attractive

01:00:15.160 --> 01:00:16.160
to the Israelis.

01:00:16.160 --> 01:00:20.160
Ethnic cleansing solves the apartheid problem.

01:00:20.160 --> 01:00:23.160
What Tom was challenging me on a minute ago

01:00:24.160 --> 01:00:28.160
and it solves the Hamas problem which he's challenging me on now.

01:00:37.160 --> 01:00:40.160
Many democratic legislators who have traditionally

01:00:40.160 --> 01:00:44.160
been very supportive of Israel have called on Netanyahu

01:00:44.160 --> 01:00:45.160
to be replaced.

01:00:46.160 --> 01:00:50.160
To what extent would things change in Gaza

01:00:51.160 --> 01:00:54.160
and the Israeli military operation in Gaza

01:00:54.160 --> 01:00:58.160
if Netanyahu is replaced as many democratic lawmakers

01:00:58.160 --> 01:01:00.160
and indeed Brett Stevens at the New York Times

01:01:00.160 --> 01:01:03.160
has called for Netanyahu to be removed?

01:01:03.160 --> 01:01:05.160
How would things change?

01:01:05.160 --> 01:01:06.160
Not at all.

01:01:07.160 --> 01:01:10.160
This is an argument that I hear in the United States

01:01:10.160 --> 01:01:12.160
and it's made by liberal American Jews,

01:01:12.160 --> 01:01:14.160
people like Tom Friedman.

01:01:14.160 --> 01:01:15.160
At the New York Times?

01:01:15.160 --> 01:01:17.160
Yeah, at the New York Times.

01:01:17.160 --> 01:01:22.160
People who believe that Netanyahu is an anomaly

01:01:23.160 --> 01:01:25.160
and if we can only get rid of him

01:01:25.160 --> 01:01:27.160
and replace him with Thomas Jefferson

01:01:27.160 --> 01:01:29.160
or somebody like that,

01:01:29.160 --> 01:01:32.160
Israel will live happily ever after.

01:01:33.160 --> 01:01:36.160
This is a foolish argument, right?

01:01:36.160 --> 01:01:41.160
It's quite clear that Netanyahu and his war cabinet

01:01:41.160 --> 01:01:46.160
and most of the national security elite in Israel today

01:01:46.160 --> 01:01:51.160
agree with Israeli policy under Netanyahu.

01:01:51.160 --> 01:01:55.160
So it wouldn't change anything.

01:01:55.160 --> 01:01:58.160
It would change hardly anything.

01:01:58.160 --> 01:02:02.160
Now you say Israel has had Iran in its sights for a long time,

01:02:02.160 --> 01:02:05.160
but isn't it true that Iran's sheer theocracy

01:02:05.160 --> 01:02:08.160
has also had Israel in its sights for a long time?

01:02:08.160 --> 01:02:10.160
After all, many of their leaders have declared

01:02:10.160 --> 01:02:13.160
the eradication of Israel off the face of the map.

01:02:13.160 --> 01:02:20.160
Look, there's no question that Iran

01:02:20.160 --> 01:02:24.160
considers Israel to be a mortal enemy

01:02:24.160 --> 01:02:28.160
and would like to do away with the Jewish state

01:02:28.160 --> 01:02:33.160
the same way Hezbollah would like to do away with the Jewish state.

01:02:33.160 --> 01:02:35.160
So there's no question about that.

01:02:35.160 --> 01:02:38.160
And there's no question that the Israelis

01:02:38.160 --> 01:02:41.160
hate the Iranians or hate Iran

01:02:41.160 --> 01:02:46.160
and it's a case of mutual hatred,

01:02:46.160 --> 01:02:48.160
mutual dislike, call it what you want.

01:02:48.160 --> 01:02:49.160
There's no question about it.

01:02:49.160 --> 01:02:52.160
Who is responsible for starting this?

01:02:52.160 --> 01:02:55.160
The implication of your question was that

01:02:55.160 --> 01:02:59.160
it is Iran that's responsible, not Israel.

01:02:59.160 --> 01:03:01.160
What we'll say later is that talk about this,

01:03:01.160 --> 01:03:04.160
about eradicating Israel off the face of the earth.

01:03:04.160 --> 01:03:05.160
It's pretty provocative, isn't it?

01:03:05.160 --> 01:03:06.160
I agree.

01:03:06.160 --> 01:03:08.160
That's correct, but I'm just saying

01:03:08.160 --> 01:03:10.160
it's not clear that they started it.

01:03:10.160 --> 01:03:13.160
You want to remember that Iran once had very good relations

01:03:13.160 --> 01:03:16.160
with Israel, once had very good relations

01:03:16.160 --> 01:03:19.160
with the United States, and that even in the 1990s

01:03:19.160 --> 01:03:23.160
the Iranians were interested in improving relations

01:03:23.160 --> 01:03:24.160
with the United States.

01:03:24.160 --> 01:03:27.160
And one could make an argument that if you had gotten

01:03:27.160 --> 01:03:32.160
a two-state solution that Iran would have reconciled itself

01:03:32.160 --> 01:03:34.160
to dealing with this problem.

01:03:34.160 --> 01:03:37.160
So we haven't talked much about the two-state solution

01:03:37.160 --> 01:03:41.160
in large part because I sort of took it off the table early on.

01:03:41.160 --> 01:03:45.160
But it's very important to understand that every American president

01:03:45.160 --> 01:03:49.160
since Jimmy Carter has pushed hard on the two-state solution

01:03:49.160 --> 01:03:52.160
because we think the two-state solution,

01:03:52.160 --> 01:03:55.160
we meaning American elites, think the two-state solution

01:03:55.160 --> 01:04:02.160
is the only reasonable way to get out of this conundrum.

01:04:02.160 --> 01:04:06.160
What has to be done here is that the Palestinians

01:04:06.160 --> 01:04:10.160
have to be given self-determination.

01:04:10.160 --> 01:04:13.160
They need a sovereign state of their own.

01:04:13.160 --> 01:04:17.160
And this is what the two-state solution was designed to do.

01:04:17.160 --> 01:04:21.160
And American leaders understood that if the Israelis

01:04:21.160 --> 01:04:24.160
did not agree to a two-state solution

01:04:24.160 --> 01:04:27.160
and you did not get a two-state solution,

01:04:27.160 --> 01:04:30.160
you were going to have trouble for as far as the eye can see.

01:04:30.160 --> 01:04:34.160
You all understand, maybe the younger people in the audience don't,

01:04:34.160 --> 01:04:38.160
but what happened on October 7th is really not an anomaly.

01:04:38.160 --> 01:04:42.160
There was the first intifada, then there was the second intifada.

01:04:42.160 --> 01:04:43.160
Late 80s and early 2000s.

01:04:43.160 --> 01:04:44.160
Pardon?

01:04:44.160 --> 01:04:45.160
Late 80s and the early 2000s.

01:04:45.160 --> 01:04:48.160
Yes, 1987 was the first intifada

01:04:48.160 --> 01:04:51.160
and 2000 was the second intifada.

01:04:51.160 --> 01:04:54.160
And these were, you know, Palestinian insurrections.

01:04:54.160 --> 01:04:56.160
But, John, you could get a two-state solution

01:04:56.160 --> 01:04:58.160
with the Palestinian leadership in the West Bank,

01:04:58.160 --> 01:05:01.160
but Hamas has made it very clear as a user of your knowledge

01:05:01.160 --> 01:05:03.160
that they don't support a two-state solution.

01:05:03.160 --> 01:05:04.160
Absolutely.

01:05:04.160 --> 01:05:07.160
There's no question about that.

01:05:07.160 --> 01:05:09.160
I just want to be very clear here.

01:05:09.160 --> 01:05:12.160
This gets back to my point that Netanyahu was playing

01:05:12.160 --> 01:05:14.160
divide and conquer, right?

01:05:14.160 --> 01:05:19.160
Netanyahu had quite good relations with Hamas before October 7th

01:05:19.160 --> 01:05:23.160
because Hamas doesn't want a two-state solution

01:05:23.160 --> 01:05:26.160
and Netanyahu doesn't want a two-state solution.

01:05:26.160 --> 01:05:28.160
And from Netanyahu's point of view,

01:05:28.160 --> 01:05:32.160
the real threat was Mahmoud Abbas and the Palestinian Authority.

01:05:32.160 --> 01:05:36.160
And you notice, by the way, that the Americans have been saying

01:05:36.160 --> 01:05:39.160
that what we need to do in Gaza

01:05:39.160 --> 01:05:43.160
is put the Palestinian Authority in control,

01:05:43.160 --> 01:05:45.160
get Hamas out of the way,

01:05:45.160 --> 01:05:49.160
and put the Palestinian Authority in control.

01:05:49.160 --> 01:05:53.160
Netanyahu has made it unequivocally clear this is not happening,

01:05:53.160 --> 01:05:56.160
and that's because the Palestinian Authority

01:05:56.160 --> 01:06:00.160
has reconciled itself to a two-state solution,

01:06:00.160 --> 01:06:04.160
and that's nightmare news for Netanyahu.

01:06:04.160 --> 01:06:09.160
You say that Tehran's hand has been strengthened during this dispute,

01:06:09.160 --> 01:06:11.160
but let me put this to you.

01:06:11.160 --> 01:06:16.160
Iran is surrounded by hostile Sunni states across the Persian Gulf,

01:06:16.160 --> 01:06:18.160
since Saudi Arabia.

01:06:18.160 --> 01:06:21.160
It's fanatically anti-sheer and well-armed arch enemy.

01:06:21.160 --> 01:06:24.160
In Iraq and Syria, at least until recently,

01:06:24.160 --> 01:06:29.160
you had Iran facing large Sunni insurgencies

01:06:29.160 --> 01:06:32.160
dedicated to slaughtering the Shia.

01:06:32.160 --> 01:06:35.160
Then there's the internal unrest within Iran.

01:06:35.160 --> 01:06:38.160
A lot of younger people, a lot of younger Iranians

01:06:38.160 --> 01:06:42.160
take a more liberal view about the world and their parents

01:06:42.160 --> 01:06:46.160
and certainly the Shia clerical regime.

01:06:46.160 --> 01:06:51.160
So are you overlooking Iran's real weaknesses and limitations?

01:06:51.160 --> 01:06:55.160
Well, he only gave me 50 minutes to talk.

01:06:56.160 --> 01:07:01.160
If he had been willing to fulfill my request

01:07:01.160 --> 01:07:04.160
to be able to talk for two hours,

01:07:04.160 --> 01:07:07.160
I would have qualified my argument somewhat.

01:07:07.160 --> 01:07:12.160
There's absolutely no question that Iran has significant problems,

01:07:12.160 --> 01:07:16.160
but the thing you want to remember about Iran

01:07:16.160 --> 01:07:21.160
is that Iran is much more powerful than all of its neighbors.

01:07:21.160 --> 01:07:24.160
It has a very large population,

01:07:24.160 --> 01:07:29.160
and the human capital inside of Iran is very impressive.

01:07:29.160 --> 01:07:33.160
And if you were to look at the potential balance of power

01:07:33.160 --> 01:07:35.160
between Iran and Saudi Arabia,

01:07:35.160 --> 01:07:39.160
if they were both able to mobilize all their resources,

01:07:39.160 --> 01:07:42.160
it's a Bambi versus Godzilla situation.

01:07:42.160 --> 01:07:47.160
That's why the Saudis are so interested in the Abraham Accord.

01:07:47.160 --> 01:07:51.160
The Saudis want to jump into bed with the Israelis and the Americans

01:07:51.160 --> 01:07:57.160
because the Saudis understand that the Iranians have a lot of potential power.

01:07:57.160 --> 01:08:00.160
Whenever you want to measure the power of a country,

01:08:00.160 --> 01:08:02.160
the two things that you go to,

01:08:02.160 --> 01:08:06.160
number one are population size and number two are wealth.

01:08:06.160 --> 01:08:08.160
Number two is wealth.

01:08:08.160 --> 01:08:10.160
Wealth and population size.

01:08:10.160 --> 01:08:13.160
And if you look at the Iranian situation,

01:08:13.160 --> 01:08:16.160
they are potentially a very powerful country,

01:08:16.160 --> 01:08:20.160
which is not to take away from your points about the problems that they face.

01:08:20.160 --> 01:08:22.160
Now it's time for question time.

01:08:22.160 --> 01:08:27.160
And please, I encourage you to try to keep your questions short of the mind.

01:08:27.160 --> 01:08:30.160
But also, feel free to ask about not just the Middle East,

01:08:30.160 --> 01:08:32.160
but also Ukraine and China,

01:08:32.160 --> 01:08:35.160
about which John has spoken in great detail.

01:08:35.160 --> 01:08:37.160
First question.

01:08:37.160 --> 01:08:40.160
You've talked about how Israel now stuck in Gaza.

01:08:40.160 --> 01:08:43.160
Do you see similar trap for the US,

01:08:43.160 --> 01:08:46.160
or do they have a path forward and out of this?

01:08:46.160 --> 01:08:51.160
Well, the United States is not going into Gaza, right?

01:08:51.160 --> 01:08:54.160
I mean, we're not putting forces in there.

01:08:54.160 --> 01:08:57.160
But we are joined at the hip with Israel.

01:08:57.160 --> 01:09:00.160
We have this special relationship

01:09:00.160 --> 01:09:05.160
so that as long as Israel is bogged down in Gaza

01:09:05.160 --> 01:09:08.160
and having all sorts of problems,

01:09:08.160 --> 01:09:12.160
both in terms of dealing with the Palestinians

01:09:12.160 --> 01:09:15.160
and dealing with the wider world,

01:09:15.160 --> 01:09:18.160
it has huge consequences for us.

01:09:18.160 --> 01:09:22.160
We end up vetoing Security Council resolutions

01:09:22.160 --> 01:09:24.160
that we don't want to veto.

01:09:24.160 --> 01:09:29.160
It ends up poisoning our relations with the Egyptians and the Jordanians.

01:09:29.160 --> 01:09:34.160
So there are all sorts of spin-off consequences for us that are negative.

01:09:34.160 --> 01:09:38.160
And this is why the Biden administration, to its credit,

01:09:38.160 --> 01:09:42.160
is deeply committed to trying to figure out how to solve this one.

01:09:42.160 --> 01:09:46.160
As I said before, we'd like Mahmoud Abbas to come in, take over.

01:09:46.160 --> 01:09:50.160
Then we can get the rich Arab countries to pour money in.

01:09:50.160 --> 01:09:53.160
We can rebuild Gaza and live happily ever after.

01:09:53.160 --> 01:09:54.160
That's what we want to do,

01:09:54.160 --> 01:09:58.160
because this is not in our interest to let this go on.

01:09:58.160 --> 01:10:03.160
But the problem we face is we can't get the Israelis to go along with us.

01:10:03.160 --> 01:10:06.160
This is well documented.

01:10:06.160 --> 01:10:10.160
And the end result is, you know, no end to trouble,

01:10:10.160 --> 01:10:12.160
certainly for the Israelis, but even for us.

01:10:12.160 --> 01:10:14.160
Next question. Yes, sir.

01:10:14.160 --> 01:10:16.160
Thanks, John Lachlan McIntyre.

01:10:16.160 --> 01:10:19.160
Since Australia's security depends on the United States,

01:10:19.160 --> 01:10:24.160
do we have no option but to take sides in Gaza and Ukraine?

01:10:24.160 --> 01:10:27.160
Meaning Australia.

01:10:27.160 --> 01:10:32.160
I'm not sure what taking sides means.

01:10:32.160 --> 01:10:38.160
If you're talking about Hamas versus Israel,

01:10:38.160 --> 01:10:45.160
that's very different than talking about the Palestinians versus Israel.

01:10:45.160 --> 01:10:52.160
In other words, I know lots of people who loathe Hamas and hope Israel destroys it,

01:10:52.160 --> 01:10:56.160
who are very sympathetic to the Palestinians,

01:10:56.160 --> 01:11:01.160
who believe that Israel is committing genocide.

01:11:01.160 --> 01:11:06.160
So I would argue you can take the side of the Palestinians

01:11:06.160 --> 01:11:10.160
if you are an Australian,

01:11:10.160 --> 01:11:15.160
and you can make the argument that that's in Israel's interest.

01:11:15.160 --> 01:11:21.160
People who've argued for a two-state solution have long argued that's in Israel's interest.

01:11:21.160 --> 01:11:25.160
That's the solution. That's the argument.

01:11:25.160 --> 01:11:29.160
But if it's a choice between Hamas and Israel,

01:11:29.160 --> 01:11:35.160
Australia, certainly the government and most people who operate in the foreign policy establishment,

01:11:35.160 --> 01:11:38.160
they have no choice but to side with Israel against Hamas.

01:11:38.160 --> 01:11:40.160
